    "body": "Hello,\r\nI have trouble in using cython for file reading and preprocessing. The cython generated cpp file can be complied with my main cpp file, but when I run the program, it will throw ` segmentation fault (core dumped)` error.\r\nHere is my test.pyx file:\r\n```\r\ncdef public int file_reader():\r\n    result=[]\r\n    with open(\"haha.txt\") as f:\r\n        for line in f:\r\n            result.append(line)\r\n    return len(result)\r\n```\r\nand I want to call `file_reader` in the main.cpp file:\r\n```\r\n#include <iostream>\r\n#include \"test.h\"\r\n\r\nusing namespace std;\r\n\r\nint main(){\r\n   cout<<file_reader()<<endl;\r\n   return 0;\r\n}\r\n```\r\nMy cython version is 0.2.61 and the c++ compiler is clang4.0.1.\r\n\r\nThanks!\r\n",
